          "image": "https://www.justonecookbook.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/Mazesoba-1.jpg",
          "content": "Thinly slice 2 green onions. Cut 30 g garlic chives into 3 mm pieces. Set aside."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "HowToStep",
        "text": {
          "image": "https://www.justonecookbook.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/Mazesoba-2.jpg",
          "content": "Grind 6 g katsuobushi in a mortar until powdered."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "HowToStep",
        "text": {
          "image": "https://www.justonecookbook.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/Mazesoba-3.jpg",
          "content": "Cut 1 sheet nori into 6 mm squares."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "HowToStep",
        "text": {
          "image": "https://www.justonecookbook.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/Mazesoba-4.jpg",
          "content": "Peel and grate ginger, measuring 2.5 ml."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "HowToStep",
        "text": {
          "image": "https://www.justonecookbook.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/Mazesoba-5.jpg",
          "content": "Mince 1 garlic clove for cooking, and 2 garlic cloves for serving. Set aside."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "HowToStep",
        "text": {
          "image": "https://www.justonecookbook.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/Mazesoba-6.jpg",
          "content": "Separate 2 large egg yolks."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "HowToStep",
        "text": {
          "image": "https://www.justonecookbook.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/Mazesoba-7.jpg",
          "content": "Heat a frying pan. Add 15 ml toasted sesame oil and 227 g ground pork."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "HowToStep",
        "text": {
          "image": "https://www.justonecookbook.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/Mazesoba-8.jpg",
          "content": "Cook pork until no longer pink. Add grated ginger and minced garlic. Stir for 1-2 minutes until fragrant."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "HowToStep",
        "text": {
          "image": "https://www.justonecookbook.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/Mazesoba-9.jpg",
          "content": "Add 15 ml sake and mix well."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "HowToStep",
        "text": {
          "image": "https://www.justonecookbook.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/Mazesoba-10.jpg",
          "content": "Add 15 ml doubanjiang and stir."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "HowToStep",
        "text": {
          "image": "https://www.justonecookbook.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/Mazesoba-11.jpg",
          "content": "Add 15 ml soy sauce and 10 ml oyster sauce. Mix well."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "HowToStep",
        "text": {
          "image": "https://www.justonecookbook.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/Mazesoba-12.jpg",
          "content": "Add 5 ml sugar and 45 ml chicken stock. Simmer for 2-3 minutes, ensuring some liquid remains."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "HowToStep",
        "text": {
          "image": "https://www.justonecookbook.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/Mazesoba-13.jpg",
          "content": "Add 1.25 ml kosher salt if needed. Turn off heat."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "HowToStep",
        "text": {
          "image": "https://www.justonecookbook.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/Mazesoba-14.jpg",
          "content": "Reheat water to boil. Loosen 2 servings fresh ramen noodles and cook according to package directions. Stir occasionally."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "HowToStep",
        "text": {
          "image": "https://www.justonecookbook.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/Mazesoba-15.jpg",
          "content": "Drain noodles in a sieve, shaking off excess water."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "HowToStep",
        "text": {
          "image": "https://www.justonecookbook.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/Mazesoba-16.jpg",
          "content": "Transfer noodles to bowls. Mix 5 ml toasted sesame oil and 1.25 ml kosher salt for seasoning."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "HowToStep",
        "text": {
          "image": "https://www.justonecookbook.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/Mazesoba-17.jpg",
          "content": "Drizzle sesame oil mixture over noodles. Use chopsticks to coat well."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "HowToStep",
        "text": {
          "image": "https://www.justonecookbook.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/Mazesoba-18.jpg",
          "content": "Place seasoned pork in the center of noodles, creating an indentation. Arrange green onions, garlic chives, katsuobushi, nori, crushed garlic, and 30 ml tenkasu around the pork. Place 1 egg yolk in the indentation per serving. Serve warm. Mix well and enjoy."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "HowToStep",
        "text": {
          "image": "https://www.justonecookbook.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/09/Mazesoba-0069-I.jpg",
          "content": "Store leftovers in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to 3 days. Seasoned pork can be frozen for up to a month."
        }
      }
